Consulate General in New York held a 62 anniversary of National Day and arrival of the Consul General Guoxiang Sun, CUSCC president Mr. Zhiwen Wang attended the ceremony for congratulating\n\n

  	On September 28th evening, Chinese Consulate in New York and the Chinese Mission to the UN held a conference of joint celebration of the 62nd&nbsp; Chinese National Day, and to celebrate the new Consul General Guoxiang Sun and his wife Mrs Wang&#39;s arrival. More than 800 people attended the reception, which including Chinese representative of UN Baodong Li, and Chinese vice representative of UN Min Wang, and overseas Chinese in the United States, the representatives from business community, students and scholars. Mr. Zhiwen Wang, the Chairman of China-U.S. Chamber of Commerce also invited to attend. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;

  	&nbsp;

  	Guoxiang Sun said that although his arrival was only 40 days, but the enthusiasm and thoughtful people in New York make him feel close and warm. He was willing to work with everyone to promote the Sino-US partnership, to promote understanding of exchanges and cooperation between people in China and US, to put more efforts on enhancing the level of service for the majority of overseas Chinese.

  	Reception was fully decorated with flowers, melodious folk music, filled with festive holiday atmosphere. Reception also arranged exhibition to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the XinHai Revolution, placing all kinds of books which were greatly welcomed by guests. On the reception, Consul General Guoxiang Sun, president of China-US Chamber of International Commerce Zhiwen Wang had a cordial conversation on regional economic and trade cooperation and exchanged views on economic development. President Zhiwen Wang appreciates China&#39;s reform and opening up has made great development achievements, and will be more dedicated to China&#39;s development and promotion of Sino-US relations.
